Note: ========================================
Note: CSS Translation Tests
Note: ========================================
Note: Test suite for the CSS frontend + backend, driving the REAL current
Note: CSS translation API:
Note:   - css_lexer:  create_lexer(source) + next_token(lexer) returning a
Note:                 token whose type lives at offset 0; TOKEN_EOF (99)
Note:                 terminates the stream.
Note:   - css_parser: parse_css(source) producing a stylesheet AST.
Note:   - css_to_hir: translate_css_to_hir(source, 0) producing HIR directly
Note:                 from source.
Note:   - hir_to_css: generate_css(hir) producing CSS text.
Note: Reporting is delegated to compiler/frontend/primitives/io/display.runa.
Note: ----------------------------------------
Note: Tests:
Note:   - CSS lexing (selectors, properties, values, at-rules)
Note:   - CSS->HIR translation (preserving structure and semantics)
Note:   - HIR->CSS generation (producing valid CSS)
Note:   - Round-trip translation (CSS -> HIR -> CSS) of increasing complexity
Note: ========================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/css/css_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/css/css_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/css/css_to_hir.runa" as Frontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/css/hir_to_css.runa" as Backend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/display.runa" as Display

Note: TOKEN_EOF as defined by css_lexer.runa (Constant TOKEN_EOF as Integer is 99).
Constant TOKEN_EOF as Integer is 99

Note: HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL as defined by hir.runa (Constant ... is 10019).
Constant HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL as Integer is 10019

@Reasoning:
Per-suite counters carried by value through every test so the summary can
report total/passed/failed without global state. Mirrors the TestResults
shape used by the peer CSS round-trip suite for grep-compatible reporting.
@End Reasoning
Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

Note: ========================================
Note: Reporting helpers
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Banner printed once at suite start.
@End Reasoning
Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "=== CSS Translation Test Suite ==="
    proc display_string with "==================================="
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[PASS] <name>" line; increments total + passed on the by-reference results
block (counters at offsets 0/8/16).
@End Reasoning
Process called "record_pass" takes results as Integer, test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let total be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, total plus 1
    Let passed be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, passed plus 1
    proc display_string_continuing with "[PASS] "
    proc display_string with test_name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[FAIL] <name>: <reason>" line; increments total + failed on the results
block so failure logs pinpoint the responsible stage.
@End Reasoning
Process called "record_fail" takes results as Integer, test_name as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    Let total be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, total plus 1
    Let failed be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, failed plus 1
    proc display_string_continuing with "[FAIL] "
    proc display_string_continuing with test_name
    proc display_string_continuing with ": "
    proc display_string with reason
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block reading counters through type-checked field access.
@End Reasoning
Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    proc display_string with "==================================="
    proc display_string with "Test Results:"
    proc display_string_continuing with "Total: "
    proc display_integer with results.total
    proc display_string_continuing with "Passed: "
    proc display_integer with results.passed
    proc display_string_continuing with "Failed: "
    proc display_integer with results.failed
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Local helpers
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Counts tokens the CSS lexer produces for a source string by driving the
real create_lexer + next_token pair. next_token returns a token object
whose type field lives at offset 0; the loop stops on TOKEN_EOF (99) and
excludes the EOF token from the count. Proves the lexer's sub-state
machines (identifier, number, hash, string, at-rule, comment scanners)
advance the cursor as expected.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_tokens" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc create_lexer from Lexer with source
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be 0
    Let token be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
    While token is not equal to 0:
        Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with token, 0
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF:
            Break
        End If
        Set count to count plus 1
        Set token to proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
    End While

    Return count
End Process

@Reasoning:
Drives one CSS -> HIR -> CSS round-trip for a fragment. parse_css proves the
fragment is syntactically valid, translate_css_to_hir lowers it, generate_css
re-emits it, and a second parse_css proves the emitted CSS is itself valid
(structural round-trip). Any stage returning 0 is recorded as the failing
stage so logs pinpoint the responsible component.
@End Reasoning
Process called "round_trip" takes source as Integer, test_name as Integer, results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ast1 be proc parse_css from Parser with source
    If ast1 is equal to 0:
        proc record_fail with results, test_name, "Initial parse failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir1 be proc translate_css_to_hir from Frontend with source, 0
    If hir1 is equal to 0:
        proc record_fail with results, test_name, "Translation to HIR failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let generated be proc generate_css from Backend with hir1
    If generated is equal to 0:
        proc record_fail with results, test_name, "Generation from HIR failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast2 be proc parse_css from Parser with generated
    If ast2 is equal to 0:
        proc record_fail with results, test_name, "Re-parse failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with generated
        Return 0
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with generated
    proc record_pass with results, test_name
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Lexer Tests
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies the CSS lexer produces at least 12 tokens for a one-rule
stylesheet with two declarations (".button { color: #fff; font-size: 16px;
}"). The minimum count (12) is the structural floor: . button { color :
#fff ; font-size : 16px ; } -- anything less means the lexer fused or
dropped tokens.
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_css_lexer" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let token_count be proc count_tokens with ".button { color: #fff; font-size: 16px; }"
    If token_count is greater than or equal to 12:
        proc record_pass with results, "CSS lexer tokenization"
    Otherwise:
        proc record_fail with results, "CSS lexer tokenization", "insufficient tokens"
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Parser Tests
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies parse_css builds a non-null stylesheet AST root from
"h1 { color: red; }".
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_css_parser" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ast be proc parse_css from Parser with "h1 { color: red; }"
    If ast is not equal to 0:
        proc record_pass with results, "CSS parser stylesheet"
    Otherwise:
        proc record_fail with results, "CSS parser stylesheet", "parse_css returned null"
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: CSS->HIR Translation Tests
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies the CSS->HIR pipeline produces a dictionary-shaped HIR for the
canonical minimal rule "p { margin: 0; }". The dictionary-type check
(HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL == 10019) catches a regression where the translator
returns a non-null but malformed HIR node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_css_to_hir" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_node be proc translate_css_to_hir from Frontend with "p { margin: 0; }", 0
    If hir_node is equal to 0:
        proc record_fail with results, "CSS->HIR translation", "translate returned null"
        Return 1
    End If

    proc record_pass with results, "CSS->HIR translation"

    Let node_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir_node
    If node_type is equal to HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL:
        proc record_pass with results, "HIR node type (dictionary)"
    Otherwise:
        proc record_fail with results, "HIR node type", "not a dictionary literal"
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: HIR->CSS Generation Tests
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Reverse direction: construct a minimal stylesheet HIR by hand using the real
HIR builder API (create_hir_dictionary_literal, create_hir_string_literal,
create_hir_list_literal, add_dictionary_entry, add_list_element) and verify
generate_css produces non-null output. This is the only test that does not
depend on the frontend, so a parser bug cannot mask an emitter regression.
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_hir_to_css" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_stylesheet be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR

    Let type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "stylesheet"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_stylesheet, "type", type_value

    Let rules_list be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR

    Let rule_dict be proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR
    Let rule_type_value be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "rule"
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with rule_dict, "type", rule_type_value

    Let selectors_list be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
    Let selector_lit be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with "div"
    proc add_list_element from HIR with selectors_list, selector_lit
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with rule_dict, "selectors", selectors_list

    Let declarations_list be proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with rule_dict, "declarations", declarations_list

    proc add_list_element from HIR with rules_list, rule_dict
    proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with hir_stylesheet, "rules", rules_list

    Let generated_css be proc generate_css from Backend with hir_stylesheet
    If generated_css is not equal to 0:
        proc record_pass with results, "HIR->CSS generation"
    Otherwise:
        proc record_fail with results, "HIR->CSS generation", "generate_css returned null"
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Round-Trip Tests
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Round-trip checks of increasing complexity covering: two declarations on a
single element, compound selectors (class + combinator + tag.class +
pseudo-class), a nested @media at-rule, and CSS function calls (rgb/calc)
inside property values. Each surfaces a distinct class of emitter or parser
regression.
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_round_trips" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    proc round_trip with "body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }", "Round-trip simple rule", results
    proc round_trip with ".container > div.item:hover { background: #f0f0f0; }", "Round-trip complex selectors", results
    proc round_trip with "@media screen and (max-width: 768px) { body { font-size: 14px; } }", "Round-trip at-rules", results
    proc round_trip with "div { background: rgb(255, 0, 0); width: calc(100% - 20px); }", "Round-trip CSS functions", results
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Test Runner
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver. Initializes a TestResults record, runs every test against
it (lexer, parser, CSS->HIR, HIR->CSS, four round-trips), prints the summary,
and returns the failed-assertion count (0 == all passed).
@End Reasoning
Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_css_lexer with results
    proc test_css_parser with results
    proc test_css_to_hir with results
    proc test_hir_to_css with results
    proc test_round_trips with results

    proc print_results with results

    Return results.failed
End Process

@Reasoning:
External integration hook callable from a top-level test runner. Forwards to
main and returns the failed-assertion count.
@End Reasoning
Process called "test_css_translation" takes nothing returns Integer:
    Return proc main
End Process
